@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{elfeed-extras.el} extends @samp{elfeed}, the Emacs RSS/Atom feed reader, with convenience commands for reading, filtering, and managing feed entries. The package depends on @samp{elfeed} and @samp{elfeed-show}.

The extensions address several common workflows:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Reading in EWW@.} Opening feed entries in the built-in EWW browser with automatic readability mode, providing a cleaner reading experience than many raw web pages (@ref{Reading entries}).
@item
@strong{Entry management.} Marking all entries as read, copying entry URLs, and adding entries to a bibliography via @samp{zotra} (@ref{Entry management}).
@item
@strong{Filtering.} Toggling between showing all entries and only unread ones, or filtering by specific tags like ``wiki'' (@ref{Filtering}).
@item
@strong{Background updates.} Updating feeds even when Elfeed buffers are not open (@ref{Background update}).
@item
@strong{Follow mode.} Automatically displaying entries as you move through the search buffer, similar to @code{org-agenda-follow-mode} (@ref{Follow mode}).
@end itemize

