@node Filtering and display helpers
@section Filtering and display helpers

@findex elfeed-extras-filter-tags
@findex elfeed-extras-display-buffer
@findex elfeed-extras-follow-entry
@findex elfeed-extras-disable-undo
The function @code{elfeed-extras-filter-tags} applies a filter string to the search buffer via @code{elfeed-search-set-filter} and displays a message indicating the active filter.

The function @code{elfeed-extras-display-buffer} shows a buffer in the other window without selecting it, using @code{pop-to-buffer}. It is used internally by the follow mode commands (@ref{Follow mode}).

The function @code{elfeed-extras-follow-entry} implements the core follow mode logic: it moves by LINES, recenters, displays the entry, and returns focus to the search buffer.

The function @code{elfeed-extras-disable-undo} sets @code{buffer-undo-list} to @code{nil} in the Elfeed search buffer, disabling undo tracking to save memory. It is intended for use in @code{elfeed-search-mode-hook}.

